    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="368" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Pruyn</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 32.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 20, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of November 20 has been
                            received. The President is gratified with your success in effecting an
                            arrangement with the Japanese government for the reciprocation of
                            national, military, and naval courtesies, and the satisfaction is
                            heightened by the circumstance that the arrangement has been extended to
                            and embraced by the representatives of the other treaty powers residing
                            in Japan.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of the Navy has been informed of the arrangement, and also
                            of your desire that the Wyoming may be ordered to return to Japan in the
                            spring.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert H. Pruyn</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Yedo.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
